sec.p:
In this section, DC-DC boost converters based on impedance network are compared in terms of eight aspects: the technology used, VG, ICR, duty cycle range, voltage and current stresses, number of components, CG, and maximum efficiency. The power density and conversion efficiency of the topology are affected by many factors, such as the operating frequency, rated power, and the number of components. The distribution of indexes for several existing topologies are summarized in Table 4. The maximum efficiency in Table 4 is the value obtained in the corresponding paper.Table 4
